How To Play All Flops In 6Max Holdem Optimally

SRP LJ/HJ vs BB, HJ has on average a few % lower betting range

A+2broadways r = range 70%
A+2broadways s = range 30%
A+B+low = 70% 50% or 30% 80%-range(simplify to small bet range)
A9x and lower - 30% 50%

Kxx
3 broadway - 30% 70%
K+broadway+lower card = 70% 70%
K+2x<9 = 30% range, on FD 30% 50%

QJT 70% range
Q+broadway r = 30% range
Q+broadway fd= 70% 70%
Q+2x<9 30% 70%

JTxr 30% range
in rest 70% 70%
mono b30% 56% time, 40% x

Txxr no straight 30% 80%-100%
Txxss 30% 50%
T9xss 70% 50%

9xxr 70% 50%
9xxs 30% 60%

lower
straight - 30% 50%
otherwise 70% 50%
mono AQ9sss: 30% 30% or x

BTN/CO vs BB SRP

A+2broadway = 30% range
A+broadway = 120% 40-50% when r, 30% when fd
A+2x<9 = 30% 50%-70% r, 30% 40% fd
A+T+6 fd = 50%

K+broadway fd = 120% 50%
K+broadway r = 30% range
K+lower = 30% 70%

Qxx 30% 80% r, FD/SD 70% 50%

Jxxr no straight 30% range, FD/SD 70% 70% but need more info here (or bet around 55% )

T9x, T8x no straight 120% 50%, T7x and lower FD 70% 50%, T6x 30% range

98x 120% 50%
rest 70% 50%

8xx disconnected fd 70% 50%
8xx disconnedted r 70% 70%

7xx and lower fd/st - 30% 50%
7xx and lower r - 70% 60%

usually mono 30% 50%

SRP BvB

Sizes 25,75,x

Most boards that are favorable for SB contain 2xhigh/mid cards, straight on board almost always means high check frequency, otherwise on most boards, high small betting frequency prevails
A+broadway suited - 30 20 50
A+broadway rainbow- range small
A + low cards - simplified to 50/50 small and check
Kxx mostly small range except for when you have 2 v low cards (K43r - 40/60)
Qxx + one high card - range small, 2 small cards - 80/20
Mono boards usually go 50 small / 50 check
J high and T high average lower on 50 small / 50 check
9 high and lower start averaging around 20 small / 80 check so can simplify to check range

3b pot

SB v BTN(mostly same as SB v CO) Sizes 25,75,x

Axx range small, mono small 50%

Kxx,Qxx 70 30 0
low Qxx checks 20-30%
Jxx 40 50 10
Txx 30 70 0
<9xx 0 50 50 aprox

SB v LJ 25,70,x (mostly same as SB vs HJ)

A,K,Qxx range small
Jxx high range small, low 0 60 40
<9xx r 0 70 30, FD 0 50 50

BTN,CO vs LJ 2 flop sizes, 24% and 64%

A,K,Q,J range small
Ax small cards some 30% check
Jx small cards big 30 70 0
Tx small range, small cards 60 40 0
<9x 20 60 20 avg

good turn cards on which we continue betting v often - A,K,Q,J depending on case, v low cards, flush cards?! (T984sss 80% small bet), small card=big bet? bring in draws = big bet?, flush comes in -20%-40% checking, A usually 40% small bet
low card pairs = big bet?
JT loves to check Txx boards to infinity

